{"id":71666,"title":"The ethics of clinical trials for cancer therapy.","abstract":"Cancer clinical trials are intended to evaluate novel interventions and to improve outcomes. Such research depends on the participation of patients seeking the best options for care. The design, conduct, and analysis of trials must therefore be grounded in an ethical framework that respects and protects the interests of clinical trial participants. ","date":"2014-07-22","categories":"Neoplasms","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25046093","annotations":[{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.801318,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.797998,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Ethics","weight":0.796625,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethics"},{"name":"Clinical trial","weight":0.793949,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_trial"},{"name":"Research","weight":0.667165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.562795,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"},{"name":"Oncology","weight":0.390025,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oncology"},{"name":"Novel","weight":0.37894,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novel"},{"name":"Trial","weight":0.0554043,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trial"},{"name":"Design","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Design"},{"name":"Analysis","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analysis"},{"name":"Ground (electricity)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ground_(electricity)"},{"name":"Intervention (counseling)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intervention_(counseling)"},{"name":"Option (finance)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/w